        },
        {
          "script": "Latn",
          "is_primary": false
        }
      ],
      "remarks": "Gold export company (Directors: Mr. Rajendra Kumar Vaya and Mr. Hirendra\nM. Vaya). In 2010, assets belonging to Machanga, held in the account of Emirates Gold,\nwere frozen by Bank of Nova Scotia Mocatta (UK). The owners of Machanga have remained\ninvolved in purchasing gold from eastern DRC. Machanga Ltd last filed an annual return in 2004 and was listed as “status inactive” according to the authorities of the Republic of Uganda. INTERPOL-UN Security Council Special Notice web link:https://www.interpol.int/en/How-we-work/Notices/View-UN-Notices-Individuals",
      "addresses": [
        {
          "street": "Plot 55A, Upper Kololo Terrace",
          "city": "Kampala",
          "country": "Uganda"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "https://www.ammitto.org/entity/un/CDe.008",
      "entity_type": "organization",
      "names": [
        {
          "full_name": "TOUS POUR LA PAIX ET LE DEVELOPPEMENT (NGO)",
          "script": "Latn",
          "is_primary": true
        },
        {
          "full_name": "TPD",
          "script": "Latn",
          "is_primary": false
        }
      ],
      "remarks": "Goma, with provincial committees in South Kivu, Kasai Occidental, Kasai\nOriental and Maniema Officially suspended all activities since 2008. In practice, as of\nJune 2011 TPD offices are open and involved in cases related to returns of IDPs,\ncommunity reconciliation initiatives, land conflict settlements, etc. The TPD President\nis Eugene Serufuli and Vice-President is Saverina Karomba. Important members include\nNorth Kivu provincial deputies Robert Seninga and Bertin Kirivita. INTERPOL-UN Security Council Special Notice web link:https://www.interpol.int/en/How-we-work/Notices/View-UN-Notices-Individuals",
      "addresses": [
        {
          "city": "Goma",
          "state": "North Kivu",
          "country": "Democratic Republic of the Congo"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "https://www.ammitto.org/entity/un/CDe.009",
      "entity_type": "organization",
      "names": [
        {
          "full_name": "UGANDA COMMERCIAL IMPEX (UCI) LTD",
          "script": "Latn",
          "is_primary": true
        },
        {
          "script": "Latn",
          "is_primary": false
        }
      ],
      "remarks": "Gold export company. (Directors Mr. Jamnadas V. LODHIA – known as\n“Chuni”- and his sons Mr. Kunal LODHIA and Jitendra J. LODHIA). In January 2011, Ugandan\nauthorities notified the Committee that following an exemption on its financial\nholdings, Emirates Gold repaid UCI’s debt to Crane Bank in Kampala, leading to final\nclosure of its accounts. The directors of UCI have remained involved in purchasing gold\nfrom eastern DRC. Uganda Commercial Impex (UCI) Ltd last filed a return in 2013 and was listed as “Inactive – status inactive” by the authorities of the Republic of Uganda.  INTERPOL-UN Security Council Special Notice web link:https://www.interpol.int/en/How-we-work/Notices/View-UN-Notices-Individuals",
      "addresses": [
