        "name": "Democratic People's Republic of Korea",
        "code": "DPRK"
      },
      "effects": [
        {
          "effect_type": "asset_freeze",
          "scope": "full"
        },
        {
          "effect_type": "travel_ban",
          "scope": "full"
        }
      ],
      "period": {
        "listed_date": "2018-03-30",
        "effective_date": "2018-03-30",
        "is_indefinite": true
      },
      "status": "active",
      "reference_number": "KPe.059",
      "remarks": "Ship and commercial manager of the ASIA BRIDGE 1. Hong Kong-owned vessel, the probable “ASIA BRIDGE 1” was instructed on 19 October 2017 by Huaxin Shipping to make preparations for entry into Nampo, DPRK to receive a shipment of coal bound for Vietnam.  The “ASIA BRIDGE 1” was instructed by an unidentified employee of Huaxin Shipping Ltd. to make preparations to receive 8,000 metric tons of coal and then sail to Cam Pha, Vietnam.  The master of the vessel was instructed to cover the ship’s name and other markings using canvas while in port at Nampo.",
      "raw_source_data": {
        "source_format": "xml",
        "source_specific_fields": {
          "un:dataId": "6908693",
          "un:versionNum": "1",
          "un:entityType": "entity"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "https://www.ammitto.org/entry/un/KPe.060",
      "entity_id": "https://www.ammitto.org/entity/un/KPe.060",
      "authority": {
        "id": "un",
        "name": "United Nations",
        "country_code": "UN"
      },
      "regime": {
        "name": "Democratic People's Republic of Korea",
        "code": "DPRK"
      },
      "effects": [
        {
          "effect_type": "asset_freeze",
          "scope": "full"
        },
        {
          "effect_type": "travel_ban",
          "scope": "full"
        }
      ],
      "period": {
        "listed_date": "2018-03-30",
        "effective_date": "2018-03-30",
        "is_indefinite": true
      },
      "status": "active",
      "reference_number": "KPe.060",
      "remarks": "In 2017, Tsang Yung Yuan (aka Neil Tsang) and Kingly Won attempted to engage in an oil deal valued at over $1 million with a petroleum company in a third country to illicitly transfer to the DPRK. Kingly Won acted as a broker for that petroleum company and a Chinese company that reached out to Kingly Won to purchase marine oil on its behalf.",
      "raw_source_data": {
        "source_format": "xml",
        "source_specific_fields": {
          "un:dataId": "6908673",
          "un:versionNum": "1",
          "un:entityType": "entity"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "https://www.ammitto.org/entry/un/KPe.061",
      "entity_id": "https://www.ammitto.org/entity/un/KPe.061",
      "authority": {
        "id": "un",
        "name": "United Nations",
        "country_code": "UN"
      },
      "regime": {
        "name": "Democratic People's Republic of Korea",
        "code": "DPRK"
      },
      "effects": [
        {
          "effect_type": "asset_freeze",
          "scope": "full"
        },
        {
          "effect_type": "travel_ban",
          "scope": "full"
        }
      ],
      "period": {
        "listed_date": "2018-03-30",
        "effective_date": "2018-03-30",
        "is_indefinite": true,
        "last_updated": [
          "\n        ",
          "\n      "
        ]
      },
      "status": "active",
      "reference_number": "KPe.061",
      "remarks": "Registered owner of DPRK tanker CHON MA SAN. DPRK-flagged CHON MA SAN prepared for likely ship-to-ship transfer operations in late January 2018. The master of the DPRK-flagged motor tanker YU JONG 2 reported on 18 November 2017 to an unidentified DPRK-based controller that the vessel was avoiding a storm in advance of a ship-to-ship transfer.  The master suggested that the YU JONG 2 load fuel oil before the DPRK-flagged tanker CHON MA SAN since the CHON MA SAN’s larger size was better suited to conduct ship-to-ship transfers in a storm.  After the CHON MA SAN loaded fuel oil from a vessel, the YU JONG 2 loaded 1,168 kiloliters of fuel oil on 19 November 2017 through a ship-to-ship transfer operation. IMO number: 5936312.",
      "raw_source_data": {
        "source_format": "xml",
        "source_specific_fields": {
          "un:dataId": "6908674",
          "un:versionNum": "1",
          "un:entityType": "entity"
        }
      }
    },
