      "entity_id": "https://www.ammitto.org/entity/un/QDe.121",
      "authority": {
        "id": "un",
        "name": "United Nations",
        "country_code": "UN"
      },
      "regime": {
        "name": "Al-Qaida",
        "code": "AL_QAIDA"
      },
      "effects": [
        {
          "effect_type": "asset_freeze",
          "scope": "full"
        },
        {
          "effect_type": "travel_ban",
          "scope": "full"
        }
      ],
      "period": {
        "listed_date": "2005-08-17",
        "effective_date": "2005-08-17",
        "is_indefinite": true,
        "last_updated": [
          "\n        ",
          "\n        ",
          "\n        ",
          "\n        ",
          "\n      "
        ]
      },
      "status": "active",
      "reference_number": "QDe.121",
      "remarks": "Regional offices in Pakistan: Bahawalpur, Bawalnagar, Gilgit, Islamabad,\nMirpur Khas, Tando-Jan-Muhammad. Akhtarabad Medical Camp is in Spin Boldak, Afghanistan.\nRegistered by members of Jaish-i-Mohammed (QDe.019). Associated with Harakat\nul-Mujahidin/ HUM (QDe.008), Lashkar I Jhanghvi (LJ) (QDe.096) and Lashkar-e-Tayyiba\n(QDe.118). Banned in Pakistan. Review pursuant to Security Council resolution 1822\n(2008) was concluded on 14 Sep. 2009. Review pursuant to Security Council resolution 2253 (2015) was concluded on 21 Feb. 2019. Review pursuant to Security Council resolution 2610 (2021) was concluded on 8 November 2022.  INTERPOL-UN Security Council Special Notice web link:https://www.interpol.int/en/How-we-work/Notices/View-UN-Notices-Individuals",
      "raw_source_data": {
        "source_format": "xml",
